---
import "../styles/global.css";

const seo = {
  title: "LeetStack Chrome Extension Privacy Policy",
  description:
    "Learn how the LeetStack browser extension handles your email address and saved problem content.",
  siteUrl: "https://www.leetstack.app/browser-extension-privacy",
};
---

<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />
    <title>{seo.title}</title>
    <meta name="description" content={seo.description} />
    <link rel="canonical" href={seo.siteUrl} />
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com" />
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin />
    <link
      href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Inter:wght@400;500;600;700&display=swap"
      rel="stylesheet"
    />
  </head>
  <body class="bg-slate-50 text-slate-900">
    <main class="mx-auto flex min-h-screen max-w-3xl flex-col gap-8 px-6 py-16">
      <header class="space-y-2">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-widest text-slate-500">
          Privacy Policy
        </p>
        <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold">LeetStack Browser Extension</h1>
        <p class="text-base text-slate-600">Last updated: {new Date().toLocaleDateString("en-US")}</p>
        <p class="text-lg text-slate-600">
          We built the LeetStack Chrome extension to help you capture practice notes without
          collecting any unnecessary information. This page explains exactly what data we handle
          and how it is used.
        </p>
      </header>

      <section class="space-y-4">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold">Information We Collect</h2>
        <ul class="list-disc space-y-3 pl-5 text-slate-700">
          <li>
            <span class="font-semibold">Email address:</span> used to send you a one-time login link
            or OTP through Supabase authentication.
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="font-semibold">Problem content you explicitly save:</span> when you click
            “Save,” we capture the code, notes, or metadata you provide and store it securely on the
            LeetStack backend.
          </li>
        </ul>
        <p class="text-slate-600">
          We do <strong>not</strong> record or transmit any other browsing data, page content, or
          personal information unless you intentionally submit it through the save action.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="space-y-3">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold">How We Use Your Data</h2>
        <p class="text-slate-600">
          The data you provide is used only to create and sync your LeetStack notes so you can
          review them later in the LeetStack mobile app or web dashboard. We do not sell or share your
          data with advertisers or unrelated third parties. Supabase is our authentication provider
          and receives your email solely to deliver the OTP email.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="space-y-3">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold">Storage & Security</h2>
        <p class="text-slate-600">
          Saved content and account information are stored in our managed cloud databases (AWS +
          Supabase). Access is limited to authenticated requests from the extension or our backend
          services, and all communication occurs over HTTPS.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="space-y-3">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold">Your Choices</h2>
        <p class="text-slate-600">
          You can delete saved notes at any time from the LeetStack interface. If you would like your
          account or data removed entirely, contact us and we will process the deletion promptly.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="space-y-3">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold">Contact Us</h2>
        <p class="text-slate-600">
          Questions or requests about this policy? Email us at
          <a class="text-blue-600 hover:underline" href="mailto:leetstack.app@gmail.com">
            leetstack.app@gmail.com
          </a>
          .
        </p>
      </section>
    </main>
  </body>
</html>
